OL,7,FBetween 1999 and 2015, over 900
OL,8,Fsubpostmasters were wrongly prosecuted
OL,9,Fdue to errors in the Horizon IT
OL,10,Fsystem, which falsely suggested
OL,11,Ffinancial shortfalls in their accounts.
OL,13,FMany are still awaiting full
OL,14,Fcompensation, despite the previous
OL,15,Fgovernment announcing payouts of up to
OL,16,F#600,000 for those with overturned
OL,17,Fconvictions.
